495
00:34:17,585 --> 00:34:20,004
Nearly tripped over my feet.

496
00:34:21,380 --> 00:34:23,341
Did you call my house?

497
00:34:25,301 --> 00:34:27,178
Speak to the lce Queen?

498
00:34:28,888 --> 00:34:32,183
You'd like her.
She's a lot like you.

499
00:34:32,225 --> 00:34:33,684
All heart.

500
00:34:39,816 --> 00:34:44,028
You're on my list, pal.
Nothing's gonna change that.

501
00:34:47,865 --> 00:34:51,494
See you in the next reel, asshole.

502
00:35:39,375 --> 00:35:43,296
lt's a nice boat you got there,
movie exec.

503
00:35:43,379 --> 00:35:46,674
lt's me, the writer.
Still want to buy my story?

504
00:35:46,757 --> 00:35:50,261
l told you l'd deal. Stop by the studio.
We'll work something out.

505
00:35:50,344 --> 00:35:53,264
And who will l ask for?

506
00:35:53,306 --> 00:35:54,765
Larry Levy?

507
00:35:56,768 --> 00:35:58,728
What's Larry Levy got to do with this?

508
00:35:59,812 --> 00:36:02,106
- How do you know about Larry Levy?
- Don't you read the trades?

509
00:36:02,190 --> 00:36:05,401
New York Times business section?
He's movin' in, you're movin' out.

510
00:36:05,485 --> 00:36:08,196
You can't make a deal, they say.
Yesterday's news.

511
00:36:08,279 --> 00:36:10,198
Wait a minute.

512
00:36:11,657 --> 00:36:14,118
Can l borrow your mobile phone?

513
00:36:14,202 --> 00:36:17,789
Larry Levy.
Larry, David Kahane here.

514
00:36:17,830 --> 00:36:21,793
Guess who's making promises
about getting pictures made...

515
00:36:21,834 --> 00:36:24,462
to writers in parking lots?

516
00:36:24,504 --> 00:36:27,548
Guess what dumb
son of a bitch executive...

517
00:36:27,632 --> 00:36:31,719
is trying to take advantage of me?

518
00:36:31,803 --> 00:36:35,556
Do you realize how unstoppable
this guy is?

519
00:36:35,640 --> 00:36:37,975
You know,
l cannot wait...

520
00:36:38,017 --> 00:36:43,064
to tell the world that when Griffin Mill
can't cut the pressure at work...

521
00:36:43,147 --> 00:36:46,150
he drives out to Pasadena...

522
00:36:46,234 --> 00:36:49,153
to pick fights with writers.

523
00:36:50,488 --> 00:36:52,490
Tell Larry Levy to call me.

524
00:36:52,573 --> 00:36:58,037
The word is out that he's going to start
making meaningful pictures for a change.

525
00:36:58,079 --> 00:37:01,249
Let's forget this.
Just stop all the postcard shit!

526
00:37:01,332 --> 00:37:03,543
l don't write postcards!
l write scripts!

527
00:37:03,626 --> 00:37:06,838
- We're both wrong.
- No, you're wrong, buddy!

528
00:37:06,921 --> 00:37:09,590
You're in over your head.
That's why you're losing your job.

529
00:37:09,674 --> 00:37:11,801
Then what are you gonna do?

530
00:37:12,927 --> 00:37:15,304
l can write.
What can you do?

531
00:37:20,059 --> 00:37:22,311
l said, let's forget this.

532
00:37:27,066 --> 00:37:29,026
Ah, shit.

533
00:37:31,154 --> 00:37:33,364
Mill, you okay?

534
00:37:41,789 --> 00:37:44,625
Keep it to yourself!

535
00:37:44,709 --> 00:37:47,295
Keep it to yourself!

536
00:38:12,945 --> 00:38:14,405
Kahane?

537
00:39:35,528 --> 00:39:39,323
That's interesting.
Who's writing this movie?

538
00:39:39,365 --> 00:39:42,910
Who wrote the new ending
to Fatal Attraction? The audience.

539
00:39:42,994 --> 00:39:45,955
A million screenwriters
from the audience wrote that.

540
00:39:46,038 --> 00:39:49,876
Who's to say what it would have done
if you had left the original ending?

541
00:39:49,959 --> 00:39:53,880
You're right, but you can say that it's
done almost 300 million worldwide...

542
00:39:53,921 --> 00:39:56,257
with the new ending.

543
00:39:56,382 --> 00:40:00,011
Larry Levy, l don't believe you've met
my assistant, Whitney Gersh.

544
00:40:00,094 --> 00:40:02,680
- No, l haven't.
- lt's a pleasure to meet you.

545
00:40:04,849 --> 00:40:07,518
How's your picture?
lt just tested last week.

546
00:40:07,560 --> 00:40:11,189
lt's doing well.
lt was our first test.

547
00:40:11,272 --> 00:40:13,191
Excuse me, Walter.

548
00:40:13,232 --> 00:40:17,653
Joel, Griffin isn't in, but l think
we really have to start this meeting.

549
00:40:17,737 --> 00:40:19,989
Okay, Celia. Thank you.

550
00:40:22,700 --> 00:40:24,911
Remember a movie called D.O.A.?

551
00:40:24,994 --> 00:40:27,205
Sure l do.
Eddie O'Brien and Pam Britton.

552
00:40:27,246 --> 00:40:30,750
Disney did a remake in '87 or '88.

553
00:40:30,833 --> 00:40:33,669
l think we've got
pretty much the same situation here.

554
00:40:33,753 --> 00:40:36,214
Keep our noses clean, Walter.

555
00:40:39,675 --> 00:40:42,178
lt's a shame to waste a picture.

556
00:40:42,261 --> 00:40:46,474
Who said we're wasting the picture?
Where did that come from?

557
00:40:46,557 --> 00:40:49,352
You know what's interesting?
We're all too busy--

558
00:40:49,435 --> 00:40:54,273
Griffin, you're really late.
They're waiting inside.

559
00:40:54,357 --> 00:40:57,777
To actually rub shoulders
with the great unwashed?

560
00:40:57,860 --> 00:41:01,114
We need to give them
the kind of pictures they want...

561
00:41:01,197 --> 00:41:03,324
not the kind
writers want to give them.

562
00:41:10,665 --> 00:41:13,668
- Hello. Sorry l'm late.
- You certainly are.

563
00:41:17,672 --> 00:41:19,924
A few minutes in the office
would be fine.

564
00:41:20,800 --> 00:41:23,219
Griffin, you missed
the formal welcoming ceremony.

565
00:41:23,302 --> 00:41:26,264
You know Larry Levy.

566
00:41:26,347 --> 00:41:28,391
Of course. Hi, Larry.

567
00:41:29,809 --> 00:41:31,227
Hi, Griffin.

568
00:41:31,310 --> 00:41:33,229
Larry was able to leave Fox
a week earlier than he thought...

569
00:41:33,312 --> 00:41:35,440
and has come aboard
as of this morning.

570
00:41:35,481 --> 00:41:40,570
- Great. Let's start.
- Larry was in the middle of something.

571
00:41:40,653 --> 00:41:44,240
No, l wasn't. l was just killing time
waiting for Griffin.

572
00:41:44,323 --> 00:41:47,326
No, finish.
What were you saying?

573
00:41:47,410 --> 00:41:51,831
l was saying l've yet to meet a writer
who could change water into wine...

574
00:41:51,914 --> 00:41:54,417
and we have a tendency
to treat them like that.

575
00:41:55,501 --> 00:41:57,753
Not at this studio.

576
00:41:57,837 --> 00:42:01,757
A million and a half of these scripts.
lt's nuts.

577
00:42:01,841 --> 00:42:04,135
And l think avoidable.

578
00:42:04,218 --> 00:42:08,222
Let me ask you. When was the last time
you bought a ticket to see a movie?

579
00:42:08,306 --> 00:42:12,226
- You actually paid your own money?
- Last night.

580
00:42:12,310 --> 00:42:14,479
Pasadena. The Bicycle Thief.

581
00:42:14,562 --> 00:42:17,774
- You saw The Bicycle Thief?
- l love that. lt's a great film.

582
00:42:17,857 --> 00:42:20,651
lt's an art movie. lt doesn't count.
We're talking about movie movies.

583
00:42:20,693 --> 00:42:22,653
Jesus, people.

584
00:42:22,695 --> 00:42:25,615
l'm just saying there's time
and money to be saved...

585
00:42:25,698 --> 00:42:28,409
if we came up with these stories
on our own.

586
00:42:28,493 --> 00:42:31,496
- Where are these stories coming from?
- Anywhere. lt doesn't matter.

587
00:42:33,080 --> 00:42:35,958
The newspaper.
Pick any story.

588
00:42:39,212 --> 00:42:42,256
'lmmigrants protest budget cuts
in literacy program.'

589
00:42:42,340 --> 00:42:45,802
Human spirit overcoming human adversity.
