590
00:42:45,885 --> 00:42:48,846
Put Jimmy Smits in it and you've got
a sexy Stand and Deliver.

591
00:42:48,930 --> 00:42:52,308
- Next. Come on.
- This isn't my field.

592
00:42:52,391 --> 00:42:55,103
lt doesn't matter. Give it a shot.
You can't lose here.

593
00:42:58,106 --> 00:43:02,401
How about 'Mud slide kills 60
in slums of Chili'?

594
00:43:02,485 --> 00:43:05,863
That's good. Triumph over tragedy.
Sounds like a John Boorman picture.

595
00:43:05,947 --> 00:43:09,200
Slap a happy ending on it,
the script will write itself.

596
00:43:09,242 --> 00:43:12,870
- Bonnie. Give me the paper.
- l don't know, Larry.

597
00:43:12,912 --> 00:43:14,872
Give it a shot.

598
00:43:16,582 --> 00:43:19,961
'Further bond losses
push Dow down 7.15.'

599
00:43:20,878 --> 00:43:23,631
- l see Connery as Bond.
- That's funny.

600
00:43:23,714 --> 00:43:27,385
lt's a good thing Oliver Stone wasn't
listening to you. Where would we be?

601
00:43:27,426 --> 00:43:31,722
We would have been spared
sitting through Wall Street.

602
00:43:31,764 --> 00:43:35,435
- What did Wall Street do worldwide?
- 70, 75, maybe 80.

603
00:43:35,518 --> 00:43:38,729
$80 million,
a couple Oscars.

604
00:43:38,813 --> 00:43:42,859
l think Larry's point is well taken.
Let's move on.

605
00:43:42,942 --> 00:43:46,404
Can you give us an update
on the Taylor-Hackford project?

606
00:43:46,487 --> 00:43:48,489
Griffin?

607
00:43:48,573 --> 00:43:49,991
Yeah.

608
00:43:51,284 --> 00:43:53,828
l was thinking what
an interesting concept it is...

609
00:43:53,911 --> 00:43:58,207
to eliminate the writer
from the artistic process.

610
00:43:59,125 --> 00:44:04,046
lf we can get rid of the actors and
directors, maybe we've got something.

611
00:44:09,469 --> 00:44:10,887
Hello, Walter.

612
00:44:10,970 --> 00:44:13,264
Make yourself at home.

613
00:44:13,347 --> 00:44:17,059
Mr. Mill, l understand you were late
coming in this morning.

614
00:44:17,143 --> 00:44:19,395
You all right?

615
00:44:19,437 --> 00:44:21,063
l'm fine.

616
00:44:21,147 --> 00:44:23,274
l appreciate your concern.

617
00:44:24,692 --> 00:44:27,069
What can l do for you?

618
00:44:27,153 --> 00:44:30,865
Don't tell me you came here
to pitch me a story?

619
00:44:30,907 --> 00:44:33,326
That's exactly what l've come to do.

620
00:44:33,409 --> 00:44:36,454
lt's a good one, too.
lt's about a writer, sort of.

621
00:44:36,537 --> 00:44:37,955
David Kahane.

622
00:44:40,833 --> 00:44:43,252
Who's David Kahane?

623
00:44:43,294 --> 00:44:46,881
- You met him.
- l meet a lot of writers.

624
00:44:46,964 --> 00:44:52,553
But this writer was murdered last night
in back of the Rialto Theater.

625
00:44:52,595 --> 00:44:54,096
Murdered?

626
00:44:54,180 --> 00:44:58,226
Come to think of it, Pasadena's
as good a place to die as any.

627
00:44:59,602 --> 00:45:01,562
What's the story?

628
00:45:01,604 --> 00:45:05,691
ln 25 words or less?
Okay.

629
00:45:05,775 --> 00:45:08,611
Movie exec calls writer.
Girlfriend says he's at the movies.

630
00:45:08,653 --> 00:45:11,989
Exec goes to movies, meets writer,
drinks with writer.

631
00:45:12,073 --> 00:45:15,618
Writer gets conked and dies
in 4 inches of dirty water.

632
00:45:15,701 --> 00:45:17,995
Movie exec is in deep shit.

633
00:45:19,122 --> 00:45:21,124
What do you think?

634
00:45:21,165 --> 00:45:24,669
That's more than 25 words.
And it's bullshit.

635
00:45:24,752 --> 00:45:28,631
Pasadena homicide doesn't think so.
They've got a complete report.

636
00:45:29,674 --> 00:45:33,970
You met Kahane at the Rialto,
got drunk with him. He left before you.

637
00:45:34,011 --> 00:45:37,306
That's the last time anyone
saw him alive, except you, maybe.

638
00:45:38,516 --> 00:45:41,352
Why are you denying this?

639
00:45:41,436 --> 00:45:44,814
Well, what do the police think?

640
00:45:44,897 --> 00:45:47,650
They think it's a botched robbery.

641
00:45:49,485 --> 00:45:54,449
The window of his car was busted.
He surprised someone taking the radio.

642
00:45:54,532 --> 00:45:56,826
There was a fight, he was killed.

643
00:45:56,868 --> 00:45:59,829
l didn't kill him, Walter.

644
00:45:59,912 --> 00:46:04,459
But l went to see him.
l know l said l didn't, but l did.

645
00:46:04,542 --> 00:46:06,627
Why'd you lie to me?

646
00:46:08,504 --> 00:46:10,840
Now's not a very good time for me.

647
00:46:10,923 --> 00:46:14,469
Haven't you heard the rumors?
l'm on my way out.

648
00:46:14,510 --> 00:46:17,013
Just what l need,
a little more controversy.

649
00:46:17,096 --> 00:46:19,015
lt's not a good time.

650
00:46:20,433 --> 00:46:22,727
Look.

651
00:46:22,810 --> 00:46:26,397
l'm in charge of studio security
in every definition of the word.

652
00:46:26,481 --> 00:46:32,028
Which means it is my job to take care
of a studio executive should he be...

653
00:46:32,111 --> 00:46:35,364
under suspicion of murder
at a time when profits are down...

654
00:46:35,448 --> 00:46:37,867
and the company is vulnerable
for a takeover.

655
00:46:37,909 --> 00:46:41,078
lt is my job to keep this
very, very quiet!

656
00:46:42,497 --> 00:46:44,582
Do you want to help?

657
00:46:44,665 --> 00:46:47,543
- Of course.
- Then stop lying.

658
00:46:47,585 --> 00:46:50,171
- How many times did you meet with him?
- Once.

659
00:46:51,380 --> 00:46:53,925
- Not counting last night.
- Not counting last night.

660
00:46:54,008 --> 00:46:56,260
Why'd you go all the way to Pasadena
to meet him?

661
00:46:56,344 --> 00:46:59,263
He had an idea l was interested in.
l wanted to talk to him right away.

662
00:46:59,347 --> 00:47:04,143
Was his girlfriend a friend, too?
Think fast.

663
00:47:04,227 --> 00:47:06,854
Jesus Christ, Walter.
What is this?

664
00:47:06,896 --> 00:47:10,066
The third degree. Wait until the police
start asking questions.

665
00:47:10,149 --> 00:47:13,611
l'll go to the police now.
You come with me.

666
00:47:13,694 --> 00:47:16,030
You're acting like someone
who's guilty.

667
00:47:16,072 --> 00:47:18,074
You're not guilty, are you?

668
00:47:18,116 --> 00:47:20,368
l'm not a murderer.

669
00:47:37,593 --> 00:47:39,595
Bad news?

670
00:47:39,679 --> 00:47:41,097
What?

671
00:47:41,180 --> 00:47:44,100
The fax.
ls it bad news?

672
00:47:46,561 --> 00:47:48,146
Business as usual.

673
00:47:49,814 --> 00:47:53,609
The Hollywood system
did not murder David Kahane.

674
00:47:53,651 --> 00:47:56,821
Not the $98 million movie,
not the $12 million actor.

675
00:47:56,904 --> 00:48:02,535
Not even the million dollar deal
that David Kahane never landed.

676
00:48:02,618 --> 00:48:05,705
The most that we can pin on Hollywood...

677
00:48:05,788 --> 00:48:09,250
is assault with intent to kill.

678
00:48:09,292 --> 00:48:14,130
Because society is responsible
for this particular murder.

679
00:48:14,172 --> 00:48:16,299
lt is to society we must look...

680
00:48:16,382 --> 00:48:20,136
if we are to have justice
for that crime.

681
00:48:20,178 --> 00:48:22,930
Because someone in the night...

682
00:48:22,972 --> 00:48:25,183
killed David Kahane.

683
00:48:25,266 --> 00:48:27,685
And that person
will have to bear the guilt.

684
00:48:29,228 --> 00:48:31,647
And if David were here now...

685
00:48:31,689 --> 00:48:34,233
l know in my heart
that he would say...

686
00:48:35,651 --> 00:48:38,571
'Cut the shit, Phil.

687
00:48:38,654 --> 00:48:42,617
What did you learn from this?
Did you learn anything from this?(

688
00:48:42,658 --> 00:48:45,787
And l'd say, 'Yeah, David,
l've learned a lot.

689
00:48:45,828 --> 00:48:48,790
We here will take it from here.

690
00:48:48,831 --> 00:48:53,169
And the next time we sell a script
for a million dollars...

691
00:48:53,211 --> 00:48:56,547
and nail some shit-bag producer
